external_knowledge:
- 'Orchestras' metaphorically represent 'crews'.;
- 'Musicians' metaphorically represent 'crew members'.;
- Each 'crew' (orchestra) is identifiable by a name, and each 'crew member' (musician) contributes to the collective effort under that name. The query aims to identify those orchestras with a diverse ensemble of at least two musicians.

- "filmers" is a colloquial term referring to directors;
- "latest works" indicates the most recent films in terms of release year;
- "genres of these creations" refers to the genre associated with each film.

- 'turn of the millennium' refers to the year 2000;
- 'typical earnings' refers to the average box office revenue for films released in the year 2000;
- 'high-grossing movies' refers to films with box office revenue higher than the average;
- 'unique entries' indicate removing any duplicates based on film title, release year, box office revenue, director’s name, crew member’s name, and genre name.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT ua.username, ua.first_name, ua.last_name
FROM user_accounts ua
JOIN system_logs sl ON ua.user_id = sl.user_id;

